results.name: Front-to-back insertion-permutation sequence; contains every finite sequence of distinct positive integers.
comment: Contains every finite sequence of distinct numbers...infinitely many times.
formula: Write 1. Then place 2 before 1 and then 2 after 1, yielding 21 and 12, as well as the first 5 terms of the sequence. Next, generate the 6 permutations of 1, 2, 3 by inserting 3 into 21 and then 12, from front-to-back, like this: 321, 231, 213 then 213, 132, 123. Next, generate the 24 permutations of 1, 2, 3, 4 by inserting 4 into the permutations of 1, 2, 3. Continue forever.
